<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,482,895]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis box="[197,315,792,817]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is not common on the Algodones Sand Dunes and is also found in Texas. Considering the disjunctive distribution of this species, ultimately it may represent a new species distinct from the species in Texas.
